comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-01T20:43:14.612Z",codex-agent,Issue discovered during end-to-end metadata normalization sweep when dependency fields remained the only unfillable gap.
  "2026-04-01T20:46:32.692Z",codex-agent,"Audit evidence: after full metadata normalization, scalar metadata and linked notes/files/tests/docs/learnings are complete across 369 items. Remaining gap is dependencies on 102 legacy items because current CLI lacks a dependency mutation command for existing items."
  "2026-04-01T21:23:14.248Z",codex-agent,"Implementation started: adding dependency mutation support for existing items through update command and contract surfaces."
  "2026-04-01T21:33:34.304Z",codex-agent,"Implemented dependency mutation for existing items through update surfaces: added --dep add/clear semantics and --dep-remove selector removals with contract parity in CLI normalization, shared SDK contracts, completion/help, and Pi wrapper mapping. Verification: pnpm build passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/update-command.spec.ts tests/unit/completion-command.spec.ts tests/unit/pi-agent-extension.spec.ts tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts passed (5 files, 153 tests); pm test pm-zdec --run --json passed all linked commands."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-01T20:43:14.612Z",codex-agent,Implement command-level dependency add/remove operations with ownership and history parity.
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-01T20:43:14.612Z",codex-agent,Create-only dependency seeding is insufficient for long-lived trackers that require retrospective graph hygiene.
  "2026-04-01T21:33:35.271Z",codex-agent,Dependency metadata hygiene requires post-create mutation pathways; supporting additive and selector-based removal semantics in update keeps legacy graphs maintainable without manual item rewrites.
